content:
The trip plan is designed to meet all constraints and utilize direct flights as specified. The itinerary starts in Brussels for the conference on days 1-2. On day 2, after the conference, a flight is taken to Lisbon, with day 2 counting for both Brussels and Lisbon. Lisbon is visited for 4 days, departing on day 5 to Venice. Day 5 is shared between Lisbon and Venice, arriving in Venice to cover the required days 5-7 for visiting relatives. On day 7, a flight is taken to Madrid, with day 7 shared between Venice and Madrid, covering the wedding days 7-11. After Madrid, Santorini is visited from day 11 to 13, with day 11 shared between Madrid and Santorini. Then, London is visited from day 13 to 15, with day 13 shared between Santorini and London. Finally, Reykjavik is visited from day 15 to 17, with day 15 shared between London and Reykjavik, and the trip ends on day 17 in Reykjavik.

All direct flights used are available:
- Brussels to Lisbon (day 2)
- Lisbon to Venice (day 5)
- Venice to Madrid (day 7)
- Madrid to Santorini (day 11)
- Santorini to London (day 13)
- London to Reykjavik (day 15)

The day ranges in the JSON output include the shared flight days as per the requirements, with no separate flight entries.

